She only watched Quet for a moment, then turned her focus upon Kup. She would 
leave the issue she arose up to him & to inform Rodimus. 

She then thought about Hydras. How would he take this meeting? Did she dare 
wish to tell him? 

Sighing, she could tell her energy levels were getting low. She had been 
constantly moving & had little time for recharging or refueling.  

"I leave it to you to inform Rodimus, Kup. I shall come to him." Her crimson 
optics gazed at Kup for a moment. 

She then turned to Quet. "Just inform Scourge not to touch anything. 
Otherwise, he'll have hell to pay." 

Nodding to all, even as her opitics gazed at Convoy. "Now... if you gentlemen 
will excuse me... my energy levels are low & I must return to base & 
recharge." 

Without allowing anyone to answer from any, due to her lack of patience & her 
lack of energy in dealing with this to become an arguement, she wanted to 
leave them with no choice to to do things on her terms. It was a last resort for 
her. 

She them leapt into the air & started back for base. 

Opening a com to the other bots who were with her, "Follow me, or rendezvous 
at the Predacon Base at these coordinates," she sent each of the bots the 
coordinates for the location of the base as she high tailed it back to base.

--part1_1e9.a184c3b.2c0ee02f_boundary
